exhibition_title: The Genius of Rembrandt: Selected Etchings from the Jones Collection
exhibition_description: This gallery is dedicated in its entirety to the magnificent etchings of Rembrandt van Rijn. The Genius of Rembrandt: Selected Etchings from the Jones Collection brings together a rich assortment of nearly 50 of the master’s landscapes, figure studies, portraits, and religious scenes. Because 2006 marks Rembrandt’s 400th birthday, this exhibition gives Twin Citians an opportunity to celebrate the work of this incomparable artist along with institutions around the world.
